      • readFromFile

        public static java.util.LinkedList<User> readFromFile()
        This method reads from a file that is serialized. It must be in the UserDataBase format. Therefore, it must be a created .data file for it to read properly.

        Returns:
        A UserDataBase object corresponding to the database, or null if the input is invalid.

      • writeToFile

        public static void writeToFile(java.util.LinkedList<User> db)
        This method writes to a file in a serialized fashion. The location of output is defined in the instance of this object.
        Parameters:
        db - A UserDataBase object that must be written to a file.
